.com%2Fleft-la-san-francisco-ai-startup-job-offer-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1783849861000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4f8904b3a8c16f7e8eccf8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleft-la-san-francisco-ai-startup-job-offer-2026-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20writer%20left%20LA%20for%20San%20Francisco%20to%20work%20at%20the%20AI%20startup%2C%20Corgi%2C%20after%20she%20received%20a%20cold%20message%20from%20its%20chief%20of%20staff.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Erika%20Lee)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Welcome%20to%20the%20era%20of%20the%20forever%20layoff%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Individuals%20falling%20into%20a%20pink%20slip%20vortex%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a51331fd9d92978fe6a5b37%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFor%20some%20tech%20firms%2C%20layoffs%20are%20a%20way%20of%20%26quot%3Bcontinuous%20tuning%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20business%20priorities%20change.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Tyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETech%20layoffs%20are%20a%20recurring%20feature%20of%20the%20AI%20era.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECompanies%20are%20cutting%20jobs%20while%20continuing%20to%20hire%20for%20certain%20roles%2C%20especially%20around%20AI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELayoffs%20aren't%20usually%20because%20firms%20are%20entirely%20replacing%20workers%20with%20AI%2C%20said%20one%20tech%20leader.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMicrosoft's%3C%2Fa%3E%20latest%20round%20of%20layoffs%20has%20become%20a%20familiar%20corporate%20ritual.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20the%20software%20giant%20said%20it%20would%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-jobs-cuts-across-sales-and-xbox-read-the-memo-2026-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeliminate%20about%204%2C800%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20marking%20another%20workforce%20reduction%2C%20as%20it%20remains%20profitable%20and%20invests%20heavily%20in%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilar%20layoffs%2C%20from%20Amazon%20to%20Meta%2C%20have%20rippled%20across%20tech%20over%20the%20past%20several%20years%2C%20while%20many%20of%20those%20same%20companies%20amass%20big%20AI%20budgets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%2C%20Cloudflare%20eliminated%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcloudflare-announces-1100-layoffs-amid-ai-focus-shift-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E20%25%20of%20its%20workforce%3C%2Fa%3E.%20CEO%20Matthew%20Prince%2C%20in%20a%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20op-ed%20following%20the%20layoffs%2C%20said%20the%20firm%20hadn't%20seen%20another%20US%20public%20company%20cut%20as%20deeply%20while%20growing%20by%20more%20than%2030%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYet%20what%20we%20did%20is%20likely%20going%20to%20become%20the%20norm%20over%20the%20next%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20Prince%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20appears%20other%20companies%20got%20the%20memo.%20In%20May%2C%20Cisco%20reported%20record%20revenue%20for%20its%20fiscal%20third%20quarter%20and%20said%20it%20would%20cut%20nearly%205%25%20of%20its%20workforce.%20In%20announcing%20the%20reductions%2C%20CEO%20Chuck%20Robbins%20said%20the%20firms%20that%20will%20win%20in%20the%20AI%20era%20are%20those%20with%20the%20discipline%20to%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcisco-announces-4000-layoffs-ai-driven-business-shift-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Econtinuously%20shift%20investment%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20toward%20areas%20with%20the%20greatest%20long-term%20potential.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERather%20than%20waiting%20for%20certainty%2C%20many%20firms%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceos-make-job-cuts-worries-about-economy-and-ai-impacts-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emaking%20waves%20of%20job%20cuts%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20they%20figure%20out%20how%20AI%20will%20reshape%20their%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20employees%2C%20looming%20cutbacks%20are%20becoming%20less%20a%20recession-era%20concern%20and%20more%20a%20regular%20feature%20of%20working%20in%20tech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22846c4179-f264-4b7e-bb83-c8acb65c8072%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Continuous%20tuning'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20are%20talking%20about%20cuts%20more%20often%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20name%20of%20technological%20advancement.%20Mentions%20of%20layoffs%20alongside%20AI%20on%20corporate%20conference%20calls%20have%20climbed%20from%20fewer%20than%20five%20per%20quarter%20in%202022%2C%20when%20ChatGPT%20launched%2C%20to%20more%20than%20100%20per%20quarter%20this%20year%2C%20according%20to%20an%20AlphaSense%20analysis%20of%20calls%20across%20industries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%20said%20its%20latest%20cuts%20aren't%20related%20to%20AI.%20Amazon%20has%20likewise%20said%20AI%20hasn't%20been%20the%20reason%20for%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20its%20cuts%20over%20the%20past%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Meta%20spokesperson%20referred%20to%20a%20statement%20the%20company%20issued%20about%20its%20May%20layoffs%2C%20in%20which%20it%20said%20changes%20varied%20by%20team%20and%20included%20moving%20thousands%20of%20workers%20to%20other%20priorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20firms%20in%20the%20information%20sector%20%E2%80%94%20which%20includes%20tech%20and%20media%20%E2%80%94%20are%20cutting%20back%20after%20high%20levels%20of%20pandemic-era%20hiring.%20And%2C%20because%20AI%20can%20help%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbotsitting-ai-hidden-human-labor-at-work-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eautomate%20some%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20certain%20amount%20of%20restructuring%20can%20help%20companies%20operate%20more%20efficiently.%20Those%20savings%20can%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20go%20toward%20costly%20AI%20investments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20firms%20have%20made%20deep%20cuts%20as%20they%20try%20to%20chart%20a%20path%20forward%2C%20companies%20aren't%20likely%20to%20announce%20sweeping%20layoffs%20unless%20they%20face%20an%20obstacle%20such%20as%20serious%20financial%20trouble%2C%20said%20Joseph%20Fuller%2C%20a%20Harvard%20Business%20School%20professor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20Fuller%20expects%20many%20companies%20to%20make%20smaller%2C%20recurring%20adjustments%20%E2%80%94%20what%20he%20calls%20%26quot%3Bcontinuous%20tuning.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20reason%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20that%20companies%20have%20spent%20roughly%20the%20last%20quarter-century%20relentlessly%20cutting%20costs%2C%20leaving%20relatively%20little%20fat%20left%20to%20trim.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fy7Q7w%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Line%20chart%20of%20the%20rate%20of%20layoffs%20and%20discharges%20in%20the%20information%20sector%20since%202016%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fy7Q7w%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20is%20uncertainty.%20Companies%20don't%20yet%20know%20how%20AI%20will%20play%20out%2C%20and%20for%20all%20the%20talk%20of%20companies%20mustering%20agents%20to%20take%20on%20loads%20of%20employees'%20work%2C%20not%20much%20has%20changed%2C%20he%20said%2C%20because%20many%20tools%20are%20still%20in%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20CEOs'%20worries%20about%20rivals%20are%20also%20feeding%20a%20need%20to%20%26quot%3Bconstantly%20reevaluate%2C%26quot%3B%20Fuller%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20they%20keep%20just%20doing%20incremental%20things%2C%20and%20they've%20got%20a%20key%20competitor%20that%20goes%20all-in%2C%20they%20can%20wake%20up%20one%20morning%20and%20be%20down%2021-nothing%20before%20kickoff%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20competitive%20pressure%20is%20pushing%20executives%20to%20make%20workforce%20decisions.%20%26quot%3BThis%20uncertainty%2C%20I%20think%2C%20will%20tend%20to%20skew%20to%20layoffs%2C%26quot%3B%20Fuller%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e1ff3f82-385a-4e47-81b2-fdc2828289d3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFinding%20rare%20AI%20talent%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20many%20cases%2C%20the%20layoffs%20aren't%20because%20employers%20are%20entirely%20replacing%20workers%20with%20AI%2C%20said%20Carrol%20Chang%2C%20CEO%20of%20Andela%2C%20which%20connects%20AI%20engineering%20talent%20to%20companies.%20Instead%2C%20she%20said%2C%20many%20boards%20are%20increasingly%20pressuring%20management%20teams%20to%20demonstrate%20AI-driven%20productivity%20gains%20without%20dramatically%20increasing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-token-economy-spending-workplace-budgets-usage-caps-software-engineer-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espending%20on%2C%20for%20example%2C%20tokens%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20few%20big%20firms%20have%20reached%20the%20point%20where%20AI%20allows%20them%20to%20operate%20with%20a%20substantially%20smaller%20workforce%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20assuming%20AI%20can%20immediately%20replace%20workers%2C%20Chang%20said%20companies%20would%20often%20be%20better%20served%20by%20helping%20existing%20employees%20learn%20how%20to%20use%20the%20technology%20effectively.%20In%20part%2C%20she%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esaid%2C%20that's%20because%20it's%20hard%20for%20companies%20to%20hire%20the%20talent%20they%20want.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTruly%20AI%20native%20and%20AI-fluent%20workers%20are%20incredibly%20scarce%2C%20and%20when%20you%20can%20find%20them%2C%20they're%20incredibly%20expensive%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegardless%20of%20the%20cause%2C%20workers%20are%20feeling%20the%20impact%20of%20looming%20pink%20slips.%20After%20leaks%20prompted%20Meta%20to%20announce%20in%20April%20that%20it%20would%20lay%20off%20workers%20about%20a%20month%20later%2C%20one%20worker%20described%20the%20interim%20period%20as%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-employees-react-to-pending-job-cuts-layoffs-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E28%20days%20of%20hell%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoyan%20Chen%2C%20a%20data%20scientist%20who%20was%20laid%20off%20from%20Meta%20as%20part%20of%20its%20May%20cuts%2C%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20when%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdata-scientist-meta-layoff-rethinking-career-path-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elayoff%20she'd%20been%20fretting%20over%3C%2Fa%3E%20finally%20came%2C%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20more%20like%20relief%20than%20pain.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2202117b57-b49a-4492-80df-a223c37bc9ed%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20cost%20of%20perpetual%20cuts%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiny-teams-era-is-here-ai-powered-startups-are-winning-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESmaller%20teams%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20reduce%20inefficiencies%20and%20layers%20of%20middle%20management.%20However%2C%20some%20companies%20are%20realizing%20they've%20gone%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etoo%20far%20and%20have%20had%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsneaky-truth-ai-layoffs-switcheroo-meta-microsoft-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erehire%20for%20roles%3C%2Fa%3E%20they%20eliminated%2C%20hoping%20AI%20could%20do%20the%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepeatedly%20laying%20off%20workers%20and%20hiring%20replacements%20can%20be%20an%20expensive%20cycle%2C%20given%20the%20costs%20of%20severance%2C%20recruiting%2C%20training%2C%20and%20extra%20contractors%2C%20said%20Jeffrey%20Pfeffer%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Stanford%20University's%20Graduate%20School%20of%20Business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20recurring%20layoffs%20remain%20a%20management%20strategy%20rather%20than%20a%20recession%20tactic%2C%20companies%20could%20be%20underestimating%20what%20they're%20giving%20up%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPfeffer%20said%20repeated%20rounds%20of%20layoffs%20create%20lasting%20uncertainty%20inside%20organizations%2C%20encouraging%20top%20performers%20to%20leave%20while%20weakening%20the%20relationships%20and%20institutional%20knowledge%20that%20make%20companies%20effective.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20company%20rehires%20people%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20coordination%20and%20communication%20is%20not%20going%20to%20be%20what%20it%20was%20if%20you%20had%20worked%20together%20for%20a%20while.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarvard's%20Fuller%20said%20that%20as%20AI%20takes%20on%20more%20work%2C%20companies%20will%20need%20more%2C%20not%20fewer%2C%20people%20with%20a%20strong%20contextual%20understanding%20of%20company%20processes%2C%20markets%2C%20competitors%2C%20customers%2C%20suppliers%2C%20and%20industry%20regulations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20need%20to%20keep%20people%20who%20know%20what%20they're%20talking%20about%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-tech-companies-keep-doing-layoffs-ai-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1783849621000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a51331fd9d92978fe6a5b37%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-tech-companies-keep-doing-layoffs-ai-2026-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Tech%20layoffs%20are%20becoming%20a%20recurring%20feature%20of%20the%20AI%20era%20as%20companies%20repeatedly%20reshape%20their%20workforces%20while%20investing%20in%20the%20tech.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tparadis%40businessinsider.com%20(Tim%20Paradis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20chauffeur%20execs%20as%20a%20side%20hustle.%20I%20rely%20on%20their%20tips%20more%20than%20base%20pay%20to%20make%20money.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228056%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Black%20sedans%20and%20SUVs%20sit%20parked%20on%20a%20street%20as%20a%20cyclist%20rides%20by.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a50f7639d0a41df475c82c7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225198%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20chauffeur%20who%20works%20for%20a%20black%20car%20service%20says%20tips%20are%20essential%20to%20his%20earnings.%3Cp%3EBernd%20von%20Jutrczenka%2Fpicture%20alliance%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-gig-workers-make-uber-doordash-taskrabit-earnings-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGig%20workers%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0from%20Uber%20drivers%20to%20delivery%20workers%2C%20say%20that%20tips%20are%20a%20big%20part%20of%20their%20earnings.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOne%20chauffeur%20in%20Florida%20said%20it's%20also%20true%20for%20his%20side%20hustle%20at%20a%20black%20car%20service.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20job%20involves%20driving%20executives%20and%20pilots%20to%20and%20from%20airports%2C%20the%20driver%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Marcus%20Thompson%2C%20a%20chauffeur%20in%20Tampa%2C%20Florida.%20The%20interview%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%20Business%20Insider%20verified%20the%20earnings%20information.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fman-moved-home-after-getting-laid-off-and-is-happier-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETampa%20area%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20about%20eight%20years%20now.%20I%20moved%20down%20here%20to%20work%20in%20film.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20jobs%20in%20that%20industry%20slowed%20to%20a%20crawl%20here%20around%202023%2C%20I%20turned%20back%20to%20a%20gig%20I%20was%20familiar%20with%3A%20chauffeur.%20I%20had%20done%20that%20work%20before%20in%20New%20York%2C%20so%20I%20was%20used%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20me%2C%20the%20job%20is%20mostly%20driving%20a%20luxury%20SUV%20or%20sedan%20and%20providing%20chauffeur%20service%20in%20professional%20black-tie%20attire.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20work%20for%20a%20company%20that%20provides%20the%20cars%20and%20coordinates%20the%20rides%2C%20but%20I'm%20a%20gig%20worker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20passengers%20are%20mostly%20executives%20going%20to%20or%20from%20the%20airport%20Friday%20through%20Sunday.%20The%20weekends%20are%20my%20busiest%20days.%20I%20pick%20up%20pilots%20who%20are%20moving%20between%20airports%20on%20weekdays%2C%20though.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20work%20as%20a%20chauffeur%20part-time%20and%20make%20about%20%2410%2C000%20a%20year%20from%20that.%20That's%20a%20lot%20less%20than%20I%20made%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-to-new-york-job-partner-stayed-behind-compromise-relationship-2026-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENew%20York%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%2010%20years%20ago%2C%20driving%20stretch%20limos.%20There%2C%20I%20would%20make%20between%20%241%2C000%20and%20%242%2C000%20on%20a%20weekend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20reason%20for%20the%20difference%20is%20that%20customers%20tipped%20me%20directly%20at%20my%20old%20gig%20in%20New%20York.%20The%20hourly%20wage%20was%20low%2C%20but%20the%20company%20I%20worked%20for%20there%20said%20upfront%20that%20about%2080%25%20of%20what%20you%20made%20came%20from%20tips.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20my%20gig%20here%20in%20Florida%2C%20people%20tip%20the%20company%20when%20they%20book%20a%20ride.%20Occasionally%2C%20a%20rider%20will%20tip%20me%20in%20cash%20when%20we%20arrive%20at%20the%20destination.%20Most%20of%20the%20time%2C%20though%2C%20the%20company%20pays%20me%20around%20%2440%20an%20hour%2C%20and%20that's%20all%20I%20make.%20I%20don't%20get%20a%20breakdown%20showing%20how%20much%20of%20my%20pay%20came%20from%20tips%20and%20how%20much%20came%20from%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20I%20got%20a%20new%20job%20with%20a%20different%20chauffeur%20service.%20I%20haven't%20started%20driving%20for%20them%20yet%2C%20but%20I'm%20optimistic%20that%20I%20will%20make%20more%20money%20overall%20because%20the%20owner%20used%20to%20be%20a%20driver%20and%20was%20adamant%20that%20chauffeurs%20there%20get%20all%20of%20their%20gratuities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20a%20lot%20of%20executives%20and%20others%20who%20take%20black-car%20services%20are%20under%20the%20impression%20that%20when%20they%20give%20a%20tip%2C%20it's%20going%20to%20their%20driver.%20That's%20not%20always%20the%20case.%20I%20wish%20more%20of%20them%20understood%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20goal%20is%20to%20find%20a%20way%20to%20do%20this%20gig%20where%20my%20skill%20set%20is%20valued.%20As%20a%20driver%2C%20you%20have%20to%20deal%20with%20people%20from%20all%20walks%20of%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aabitter%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eabitter%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20via%20encrypted%20messaging%20app%20Signal%20at%20808-854-4501.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%2C%20a%20nonwork%20WiFi%20network%2C%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehere's%20our%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-guide-to-securely-sharing-whistleblower-information-about-powerful-institutions-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%