22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpower-hours-day-in-the-life-successful-business-leaders-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPower%20Hours%3C%2Fa%3E%20series%20gives%20readers%20an%20inside%20look%20at%20how%20powerful%20leaders%20in%20business%20structure%20their%20workday.%20Reach%20out%20to%20editor%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Flauryn-haas%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELauryn%20Haas%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20share%20your%20daily%20routine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchipotle-cava-thriving-consumers-prioritize-value-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EChipotle%20wants%20to%20deliver%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20consistent%20experience%20for%20our%20guests.%20As%20leaders%2C%20we%20try%20to%20be%20consistent%20with%20our%20visits.%20We%20talk%20about%20the%20food%2C%20we%20talk%20about%20people%2C%20we%20talk%20about%20the%20results.%20It's%20important%20for%20our%20leadership%2C%20too.%20I'm%20consistent%20in%20how%20I%20show%20up%20and%20what%20we%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jason%20Kidd%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4ff312d3a449ec3445fe39%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221365%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKidd%20said%20consistency%20is%20a%20top%20priority.%3Cp%3EMarissa%20Leshnov%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220f7b0710-da78-4009-8ed0-37edbadf7103%5C%22%3EI%20travel%20two%20to%20three%20days%20a%20week%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20rather%20fly%20in%20the%20morning%2C%20and%20I%20like%20to%20go%20through%20TSA%20about%2030%20minutes%20before%20we%20board.%20I%20get%20to%20the%20airport%20at%20the%20very%20last%20minute.%20It's%20important%20to%20pack%20as%20much%20patience%20as%20possible%20when%20traveling.%20Nothing%20goes%20to%20plan%2C%20and%20you%20have%20to%20make%20the%20most%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20usually%20back%20from%20traveling%20on%20most%20weekends%20and%20on%20Mondays%20and%20Fridays.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20give%20my%20family%20a%20lot%20of%20credit%2C%20especially%20my%20wife.%20We've%20been%20together%20for%2027%20years.%20I%20wouldn't%20be%20nearly%20as%20successful%20if%20it%20weren't%20for%20her.%20We%20plan%20family%20vacations%20in%20advance%20and%20are%20very%20careful%20about%20taking%20them%20a%20couple%20of%20times%20a%20year.%20When%20I'm%20home%2C%20I'm%20present%20and%20intentional.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221d333760-6347-464f-9df8-e99f32cdea15%5C%22%3EI%20wake%20up%20before%206%20a.m.%20and%20exercise%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETaking%20care%20of%20myself%20is%20important.%20I%20usually%20work%20out%20between%206%20a.m.%20and%207%20a.m.%20I%20do%20strength%20exercise%20two%20days%20a%20week%20and%20cardio%20three%20days%20a%20week.%20I%20try%20to%20stay%20active%2C%20break%20a%20sweat%2C%20get%20the%20blood%20flowing.%20Travel%20is%20a%20huge%20part%20of%20the%20job%2C%20so%20I%20have%20to%20stay%20healthy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I'm%20working%20out%2C%20I%20listen%20to%20the%20Wall%20Street%20Journal's%20%26quot%3BWhat's%20News%26quot%3B%20podcast.%20It%20sets%20a%20good%20perspective%20on%20what's%20going%20on%20for%20the%20day%2C%20and%20I%20may%20read%20some%20articles%20that%20interest%20me.%20Then%20I'll%20go%20back%20and%20reference%20those%20later%20on%20in%20the%20morning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226c8cd513-9b8a-45f6-aab9-b877e7866d10%5C%22%3EI%20have%20a%20post-workout%20coffee%20and%20a%20small%20breakfast%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20my%20workout%2C%20I%20have%20a%20black%20coffee%20with%20a%20splash%20of%20cream%20and%20a%20small%20protein-based%20breakfast.%20I'm%20going%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchipotle-price-changes-core-customer-shaped-economy-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eeating%20Chipotle%20all%20day%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20I%20taste%20food%20at%20every%20restaurant%2C%20sampling%20guac%2C%20salsa%2C%20and%20proteins.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESo%20I%20make%20sure%20my%20breakfast%20is%20fairly%20light.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20first%20things%20I%20review%20at%20that%20time%20is%20our%20sales%20report%20from%20the%20day%20before.%20That%20gives%20me%20a%20snapshot%20of%20trends%2C%20how%20the%20business%20is%20performing%2C%20and%20what%20might%20need%20my%20attention%20that%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e943466b-0066-4a5d-9c86-35fb2dfea7a3%5C%22%3EI%20visit%20the%20first%20restaurant%20before%209%20a.m.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20like%20to%20get%20into%20a%20restaurant%20before%209%20a.m.%20because%20I%20start%20the%20day%20while%20they're%20doing%20prep.%20I%20stay%20through%20opening%20at%2010%3A45%20a.m..%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20Chipotle%20restaurant%20prepares%20fresh%20food%20every%20day.%20They're%20hand-smashing%20guacamole.%20There's%20no%20can%20openers%2C%20no%20shortcuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20allows%20me%20to%20really%20see%20how%20the%20team%20is%20doing.%20The%20foundation%20for%20making%20a%20great%20day%20is%20making%20sure%20the%20prep%20goes%20well%20in%20the%20back%20of%20the%20house%2C%20shoulder%20to%20shoulder%2C%20tasting%20the%20food%2C%20observing%20preparation%2C%20and%20spending%20time%20with%20the%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20go%20over%20KPIs%20for%20that%20specific%20restaurant%20and%20for%20the%20region%20or%20local%20area.%20We%20really%20interact%20with%20the%20people%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20they're%20genuinely%20interested%20in%20what%20they're%20doing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jason%20Kidd%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4ff399d3b3e4576519727e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221365%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKidd%20arrives%20to%20his%20first%20restaurant%20before%209%20a.m.%3Cp%3EMarissa%20Leshnov%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229a082e1d-1a5f-4711-a54d-2d72369bd973%5C%22%3EConsistency%20is%20a%20priority%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKPIs%20are%20important%2C%20but%20showing%20consistency%20is%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20first%20couple%20of%20hours%20in%20the%20restaurant%2C%20I%20love%20listening%20and%20observing%20what's%20working%2C%20what's%20not%2C%20and%20where%20teams%20need%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20look%20for%20two%20key%20things%20at%20restaurants%3A%20Food%20and%20people.%20Is%20the%20food%20right%3F%20Are%20the%20people%20right%3F%20When%20I%20say%20people%2C%20I'm%20referring%20to%20our%20team%20members%2C%20our%20restaurant%20managers%2C%20and%20our%20guests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20we%20promoted%2023%2C000%20people%2C%20so%20we're%20constantly%20identifying%20internal%20talent%20during%20these%20visits.%20We%20observe%20how%20people%20show%20up%20and%20how%20they%20react.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fe488c29-992b-4fb1-a6e2-5c6cb3db3652%5C%22%3EI%20head%20to%20the%20next%20location%20for%20lunch%20at%2011%20a.m.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20after%20opening%2C%20I%20go%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fday-in-the-life-naya-ceo-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20next%20restaurant%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20go-to%20order%20is%20a%20bowl%20with%20brown%20rice%2C%20black%20beans%2C%20chicken%2C%20and%20carnitas%2C%20hot%20salsa%2C%20tomato%20salsa%2C%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20sour%20cream%2C%20some%20guacamole%2C%20and%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20lettuce%20on%20top.%20I%20eat%20it%20almost%20every%20day%2C%20and%20I%20never%20get%20tired%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221365%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chipotle%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4ff434d3a449ec3445fe54%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKidd%20said%20he%20checks%20the%20restaurants%20he%20visits%20for%20consistency.%3Cp%3EMarissa%20Leshnov%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20stand%20in%20line%20with%20guests%20and%20interact%20with%20them.%20I%20buy%20lunch%20for%20the%20people%20around%20me%2C%20tell%20them%20who%20I%20am%2C%20and%20talk%20to%20them%20about%20how%20often%20they%20come%20to%20Chipotle%2C%20what%20they%20order%2C%20what%20they%20like%20about%20it%2C%20and%20what%20we%20can%20do%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20lunch%2C%20we%20head%20to%20the%20back%20of%20the%20house%20and%20do%20a%20consistency%20check.%20We%20ask%20about%20the%20food%2C%20how%20prep%20went%20that%20morning%2C%20how%20KPIs%20are%20doing%20and%20trending%2C%20and%20what%20they%20need%20help%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2239875483-01a0-4d06-9f7d-7f6ed139b8b7%5C%22%3EI%20go%20to%20another%20location%20around%201%20p.m.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEmployees%20are%20typically%20super%20nervous%20because%20they%20want%20to%20put%20their%20best%20foot%20forward%20and%20show%20off%20what%20they%20can%20do.%20I%20try%20to%20put%20them%20at%20ease%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%20When%20somebody%20says%20they're%20nervous%2C%20my%20favorite%20response%20is%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20am%2C%20too.%20Let's%20get%20through%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20try%20to%20diffuse%20the%20nerves%20because%20the%20last%20thing%20I%20want%20to%20do%20is%20take%20away%20from%20their%20ability%20to%20do%20their%20job.%20I%20try%20to%20make%20it%20as%20informal%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ed942042-f5ad-416d-9255-2adf4ef9028a%5C%22%3EI%20spend%20about%20an%20hour%20driving%20around%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20also%20responsible%20for%20development%20and%20real%20estate.%20While%20we're%20traveling%2C%20I%20like%20to%20take%20the%20team%20to%20visit%20potential%20sites%20and%20look%20at%20new%20restaurants.%20I%20try%20to%20understand%20the%20market%20and%20get%20a%20feel%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20long-term%20goal%20is%20to%20reach%20over%207%2C000%20restaurants%20in%20the%20US%20and%20Canada.%20A%20big%20part%20of%20that%20is%20understanding%20the%20market%20and%20what's%20going%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jason%20Kidd%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4ff3d8b3a8c16f7e8ed0db%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221365%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKidd%20said%20that%20he%20tries%20to%20quickly%20put%20employees%20at%20ease%20during%20restaurant%20visits.%3Cp%3EMarissa%20Leshnov%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2269ad93c7-5a41-47f1-beef-9a381ec9c71d%5C%22%3EI%20catch%20up%20on%20calls%20and%20emails%20around%204%3A30%20p.m.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20spend%20the%20late%20afternoon%20connecting%20with%20direct%20reports%2C%20cross-functional%20partners%2C%20or%20peers.%20I%20also%20take%20time%20to%20recap%20the%20day%20with%20the%20team%20and%20determine%20whether%20any%20immediate%20action%20needs%20to%20be%20taken.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22edd020a4-72f7-4a43-aef1-810800cd6b53%5C%22%3EI%20connect%20with%20my%20family%20around%206%20p.m.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20family%20is%20incredibly%20important%20to%20me%2C%20and%20when%20I'm%20on%20the%20road%2C%20I%20try%20to%20stay%20connected.%20I%20call%20my%20wife%20around%206%20p.m.%20and%20try%20to%20reach%20my%20college-aged%20kids.%20They're%20sometimes%20hard%20to%20pin%20down%2C%20but%20I'll%20try%20to%20reach%20out%20or%20trade%20texts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2232b8668f-b020-409d-a922-b64b50213f8c%5C%22%3EI%20have%20dinner%20with%20the%20regional%20team%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I'm%20on%20the%20road%2C%20I%20often%20have%20a%20roughly%2090-minute%20dinner%20with%20three%20or%20four%20people%20from%20the%20regional%20team.%20Those%20conversations%20are%20important%20for%20getting%20to%20know%20people%20in%20a%20different%20way.%20Everybody%20has%20a%20story.%20I%20try%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20they%20want%20to%20do%20and%20whether%20they%20have%20aspirations%20to%20move%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221365%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jason%20Kidd%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4ff3f4b3a8c16f7e8ed0dc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKidd%20said%20he%20recharges%20by%20spending%20time%20with%20family%20and%20friends%20%E2%80%94%20and%20watching%20sports.%3Cp%3EMarissa%20Leshnov%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2264d99717-824e-4ab3-8bc9-ea2cc7f44a0a%5C%22%3EI%20end%20my%20night%20watching%20sports%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20an%20avid%20sports%20fan%2C%20so%20if%20there's%20something%20on%2C%20I'll%20try%20to%20catch%20the%20end%20of%20a%20game%20before%20getting%20back%20to%20the%20hotel.%20I%20may%20read%20something%20before%20going%20to%20sleep%20around%2011%20p.m.%20Then%2C%20I%20do%20it%20all%20over%20the%20next%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f5084d97-3bf7-4e40-b588-9f73d840e7ec%5C%22%3EFamily%2C%20friends%2C%20and%20time%20to%20myself%20help%20me%20recharge%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20try%20to%20interact%20with%20friends%20who%20don't%20care%20about%20what%20I'm%20doing%20at%20work.%20Talking%20to%20other%20people%20about%20what's%20going%20on%20in%20their%20lives%20re-energizes%20me.%20Exercise%20also%20helps.%20I%20like%20to%20play%20golf%20and%20travel%2C%20and%20I%20like%20to%20do%20those%20things%20on%20a%20daily%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20can%20sit%20down%20and%20watch%2030%20minutes%20of%20sports%20by%20myself%2C%20it%20also%20recharges%20me.%20When%20I'm%20running%20low%2C%20I%20need%20a%20little%20time%20to%20myself%20%E2%80%94%20and%20if%20I%20take%20that%20time%2C%20I'm%20recharged%20and%20ready%20to%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fday-in-the-life-chipotle-coo-visits-dozen-stores-weekly-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1783848481000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insi