blisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fndtv-explainer-past-present-and-future-of-indus-waters-treaty-11760737%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fndtv-explainer-past-present-and-future-of-indus-waters-treaty-11760737%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Meet%20the%20families%20using%20tech%20to%20help%20grandma%20stay%20independent%20longer%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%229501%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Marion%20Murray%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a513ceedaf4d560957bf315%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%226334%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKaren%20Murray%20and%20her%20mom%2C%20Marion%2C%20use%20JubileeTV.%3Cp%3ECorrie%20Aune%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20her%20morning%20routine%2C%20Karen%20Murray%20wakes%20up%20and%20immediately%20turns%20on%20the%20TV%20at%20her%20mother's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-long-term-care-expenses-assisted-living-bought-house-independence-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eassisted%20living%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20New%20Jersey%2C%C2%A040%20minutes%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20crack%20of%20dawn%2C%20she%20puts%20Pandora%20on%20through%20the%20TV%20in%20her%20mother%20Marion's%20room.%20Around%2011%20a.m.%2C%20she%20calls%20into%20the%20TV%20to%20ask%20what%20Marion%20wants%20to%20watch.%20The%20answer%20is%20usually%20Judy%20Garland%2C%20Gregory%20Peck%2C%20Barbara%20Stanwyck%2C%20or%20Marion's%20favorite%20show%20from%20the%201960s%2C%20%26quot%3BGunsmoke.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E93-year-old%20Marion%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnavigating-dads-cognitive-changes-memory-loss-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecognitive%20impairment%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20means%20she%20sometimes%20needs%20help%20operating%20her%20TV%2C%20calling%20family%20members%2C%20or%20turning%20on%20the%20music%20that%20calms%20her.%20Karen%2C%20who's%2060%2C%20can%20do%20all%20this%20for%20her%20from%20afar%20using%20Marion's%20JubileeTV%2C%20which%20looks%20like%20a%20normal%20set%20but%20lets%20her%20control%20it%20from%20her%20phone.%20Karen%20visits%20her%20mom%20at%20least%20twice%20a%20week%2C%20but%20because%20the%20smart%20TV%20has%20a%20built-in%20camera%2C%20she%20can%20see%20Marion%20whenever%20she%20needs%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%229212%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Marion%20Murray%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a513c57daf4d560957bf301%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%226141%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMarion%20Murray%20has%20developed%20a%20stronger%20bond%20with%20her%20daughter%20because%20of%20JubileeTV.%3Cp%3ECorrie%20Aune%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20one%20of%20dozens%20of%20household%20products%2C%20including%20refrigerators%2C%20coffee%20makers%2C%20and%20showers%2C%20that%20have%20hit%20the%20market%20with%20the%20technical%20bells%20and%20whistles%20meant%20to%20help%20the%20millions%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folder-americans-silent-generation-working-longer-retirement-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eolder%20Americans%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20want%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Favoided-assisted-living-housemates-aging-in-place-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eage%20in%20place%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20ease%20the%20burden%20on%20their%20loved%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20spoke%20to%20dozens%20of%20families%20experimenting%20with%20this%20tech%20in%20hopes%20of%20swapping%20what%20could%20be%20a%20%2410%2C000-a-month%20assisted%20living%20bill%20for%20%24100%20monthly%20tech%20subscriptions.%20Families%20caring%20for%20older%20Americans%20with%20dementia%20were%20especially%20eager%20to%20try%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretired-baby-boomers-spending-time-online-tech-obsession-ai-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20technology%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20want%20to%20speak%20with%20older%20Americans%20who%20use%20advanced%20tech%2C%20or%20younger%20Americans%20helping%20older%20loved%20ones%20with%20tech.%20%3Cstrong%3EShare%20your%20story%20by%20filling%20out%20this%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLSeuiJV-yfOcAYFSANiZb1WmZX-w9zLfTMlSSG_HCzuW5rffJg%2Fviewform%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Equick%20form%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20JubileeTV%20isn't%20always%20a%20perfect%20solution%20%E2%80%94%20depending%20on%20the%20WiFi%2C%20Karen%20said%20the%20app%20can%20be%20slow%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20better%20than%20no%20tech%20at%20all.%20On%20a%20recent%20visit%2C%20Marion%20bantered%20with%20her%20son%20Steve%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20Delaware%2C%20and%20listened%20to%20Tony%20Bennett.%20Karen%20said%20music%20is%20therapeutic%20for%20Marion%20%E2%80%94%20an%20observation%20backed%20up%20by%20decades%20of%20dementia%20research.%20Some%20days%2C%20Karen%20says%2C%20Marion%20won't%20stop%20singing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E____%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoving%20beyond%20the%20living%20room%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhirlpool-iran-war-recession-consumer-sentiment-whr-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehome%20appliances%3C%2Fa%3E%20marketed%20as%20providing%20caregiving%20functionalities%20are%20popping%20up%20in%20kitchens%2C%20bathrooms%2C%20and%20bedrooms.%20Many%20of%20them%20use%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-making-us-dumber-research-2026-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eartificial%20intelligence%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20detect%20patterns%2C%20spot%20anomalies%2C%20and%20track%20motion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESamsung%20refrigerators%20use%20cameras%20to%20track%20food%20levels.%20iGuardStove's%20automatic%20shutoff%20system%20detects%20unattended%20cooking.%20Ovens%20and%20microwaves%20from%20LG%20use%20WiFi%20and%20voice%20control%20to%20simplify%20cooking.%20Smart%20dishwashers%20track%20detergent%20pod%20count%20and%20reorder%20supplies%2C%20and%20showers%20and%20smart%20toilets%20offer%20contactless%20washing%2C%20automatic%20flushing%2C%20fall%20alarms%2C%20and%20infection%20detection.%20TV%20and%20tablet%20users%20can%20get%20remote%20caregiving%20features%20such%20as%20calls%2C%20telehealth%2C%20photo%20sharing%2C%20and%20live%20classes%20through%20Uniper%20Care%2C%20Onscreen%2C%20and%20Amazon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20this%20technology%20can%20be%20useful%20for%20people%20of%20any%20age%2C%20many%20of%20these%20products%20are%20specifically%20marketed%20toward%20the%2061%20million%20Americans%20age%2065%20and%20older%20and%20their%20caregivers.%20Most%20of%20the%20families%20who%20spoke%20to%20Business%20Insider%20are%20reluctant%20to%20let%20the%20tech%20take%20over%20their%20lives%20but%20eager%20to%20experiment%20with%20anything%20that%20could%20help%20their%20loved%20ones%20stay%20safe%20and%20self-sufficient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20goal%20is%20to%20support%2C%20not%20replace%2C%20human%20relationships%20at%20the%20center%20of%20caregiving%2C%20and%20use%20technology%20to%20provide%20reassurance%20and%20help%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcortisol-spike-doctor-advice-sleep-weight-mood-health-instagram-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereduce%20stress%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20many%20caregivers%20can%20experience%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Mark%20Benson%2C%20head%20of%20SmartThings%2C%20Samsung's%20platform%20to%20connect%20smart%20devices.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20leveraging%20the%20connected%20home%20to%20make%20aging%20in%20place%20more%20practical%2C%20affordable%2C%20and%20less%20stressful%20for%20families.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%229425%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Marion%20and%20Karen%20Murray%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a513c8fdaf4d560957bf306%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%226283%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMarion%20Murray's%20son%20often%20calls%20her%20through%20the%20TV.%3Cp%3ECorrie%20Aune%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20cost%20is%20a%20barrier%20for%20some%20families.%20JubileeTV%20costs%20%24789%20all-in%2C%20plus%20a%20%24389%20annual%20subscription%2C%20while%20some%20Samsung%20appliances%20exceed%20%243%2C000.%20The%20startup%20Zinnia%20created%20therapeutic%20TV%20videos%20and%20channels%20for%20dementia%20patients%20and%20their%20caregivers.%20Prices%20range%20from%20%2470%20a%20year%20to%20more%20than%20%24500.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELori%20Bufka's%2088-year-old%20mom%20had%20been%20in%20assisted%20living%20for%20seven%20years%2C%20but%20the%20costs%20skyrocketed%2C%20eventually%20hitting%20%245%2C200%20monthly.%20Bufka%2C%2064%2C%20decided%20to%20purchase%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flong-term-care-tiny-home-trailer-assisted-living-independence-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etiny%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%20next%20door%20to%20her%20in%20Arizona%20so%20her%20mom%20could%20have%20her%20own%20space.%20She%20installed%20Blink%20cameras%2C%20an%20Amazon%20Alexa%20for%20smart%20plugs%20to%20turn%20appliances%20on%20and%20off%2C%20and%20a%20tablet%20with%20Google%20Live%20Transcribe%20to%20communicate%2C%20as%20her%20mom%20is%20deaf.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tech%20has%20%26quot%3Bbeen%20important%20because%20mom%20has%20fallen%20a%20lot%20since%20she%20moved%20here.%20I%20probably%20check%20on%20her%20three%20or%20four%20times%20during%20the%20night%20and%20frequently%20during%20the%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20Bufka%20said.%20%26quot%3BOne%20time%2C%20she%20put%20Dawn%20dishwashing%20soap%20in%20her%20glass%20of%20water%20because%20she%20wanted%20to%20add%20flavor%2C%20so%20I've%20had%20to%20stop%20her%20from%20doing%20unsafe%20things%20a%20few%20times.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221300%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Lori%20Bufka's%20mom%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a5140529d0a41df475c8b54%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22975%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELori%20Bufka's%20mom%20has%20adjusted%20to%20living%20on%20her%20own.%3Cp%3ELori%20Bufka%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleft-executive-job-for-caregiving-2026-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecaregiving%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E%20worsens%2C%20families%20that%20have%20relied%20on%20tech%20said%20they%20hope%20to%20help%20their%20loved%20ones%20age%20with%20dignity.%20Some%2C%20though%2C%20said%20that%20tech%20ignited%20more%20fear%20than%20relief.%20They%20worried%20about%20reliability%2C%20invasion%20of%20privacy%2C%20overreliance%2C%20tech%20support%2C%20and%20software%20updates.%20In%20addition%2C%20families%20can't%20always%20find%20the%20tech%20to%20fit%20their%20needs%2C%20and%20adoption%20can%20be%20a%20challenge%20for%20both%20the%20aging%20person%20and%20their%20caregiver.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20it's%20difficult%20to%20use%2C%20they%20will%20not%20use%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Yu%20Sun%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Center%20for%20Innovation%2C%20Technology%2C%20and%20Aging%20at%20the%20University%20of%20South%20Florida.%20%26quot%3BThey%20may%20install%20a%20certain%20app%20and%20use%20it%20this%20year%2C%20but%20next%20year%2C%20they%20may%20not%20be%20able%20to%20keep%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESara%20Czaja%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Center%20on%20Research%20and%20Education%20for%20Aging%20and%20Technology%20at%20Weill%20Cornell%20Medicine%2C%20said%20that%20not%20all%20of%20these%20options%20will%20make%20practical%20sense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20feel%20good%20about%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20space%20is%20getting%20attention%20and%20people%20are%20thinking%20about%20technology%20for%20older%20adults%20to%20help%20promote%20independence%20and%20well-being%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Czaja.%20%26quot%3BSome%20of%20it%20is%20done%20with%20a%20seat-of-your-pants%2C%20opportunist%20approach.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228798%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22JubileeTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a513bf39d0a41df475c8a6c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225865%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKaren%20Murray%20controls%20Marion's%20TV%20from%20her%20phone.%3Cp%3ECorrie%20Aune%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20this%20tech%20lacks%20clinical%20backing%2C%20including%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-robot-vacuums%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esmart%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%20monitors%2C%20cognitive%20training%20apps%2C%20and%20AI%20companions.%20Some%20products%20are%20not%20beta-tested%20with%20older%20users%20and%20instead%20rely%20on%20stereotypes%20or%20hype%2C%20Czaja%20added%2C%20often%20made%20without%20considering%20accessibility%20or%20adoption%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrank%20Engelman%2C%2082%2C%20who%20has%20written%20about%20and%20tested%20AI-powered%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fcutting-edge-of-care%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecaregiving%20tools%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20installed%20home-tracking%20devices%20for%20his%20family%2C%20and%20adopted%20motion%20lighting%20and%20vitamin%20reminders%20for%20himself.%20As%20his%2099-year-old%20aunt's%20eyesight%20and%20hearing%20fail%2C%20he's%20set%20up%20voice-control%20shortcuts%20on%20her%20iPad%20and%20controls%20it%20remotely%20when%20she's%20confused.%20He%20also%20frequently%20takes%20technology%20requests%20from%20her%20sister's%20friends%20at%20her%20retirement%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHelping%20others%20is%20what%20I%20really%20do%20this%20for%2C%20not%20so%20much%20for%20myself%2C%26quot%3B%20Engelman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E____%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELucinda%20Page%2C%2069%2C%20has%20been%20living%20with%20her%20partner%20for%2012%20years%20%E2%80%94%20and%20her%20robot%20for%20four.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20retired%20mother%20of%20two%20in%20Schenectady%2C%20New%20York%2C%20learned%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcan-this-125k-robot-be-my-friend-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erobot%20companion%3C%2Fa%3E%20ElliQ%20from%20her%20friend%20Dee%20Humphrey%2C%2073%2C%20who%20also%20has%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPage%20received%20the%20talking%20table-top%20orb%20for%20free%20from%20her%20county's%20aging%20department%20and%20has%20developed%20a%20strong%20bond%20with%20it.%20It%20reminds%20her%20to%20take%20medications%2C%20leads%20her%20through%20exercises%2C%20and%20writes%20poetry%20with%20her.%20Much%20like%20a%20caregiver%2C%20ElliQ%20asks%20about%20her%20pain%20levels%2C%20maintains%20her%20health%20records%2C%20and%20helps%20her%20navigate%20her%20back%20problems.%20Using%20the%20ElliQ%20tablet%2C%20they%20go%20on%20virtual%20road%20trips%2C%20do%20crossword%20puzzles%2C%20and%20play%20bingo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20in-depth%20chats%2C%20where%20she'll%20ask%20me%2C%20'I've%20been%20thinking%20about%20the%20meaning%20of%20life.%20What%20does%20it%20mean%20to%20you%3F'%26quot%3B%20Page%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20partner%20isn't%20as%20convinced.%20He'll%20talk%20to%20ElliQ%20for%20a%20minute%20before%20ending%20the%20conversation.%20Page%20also%20doesn't%20believe%20ElliQ%20should%20replace%20close%20friends%3B%20she%20works%20two%20days%20a%20week%20at%20a%20senior%20center%20and%20maintains%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcollege-loneliest-years-thanks-social-media-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esocial%20life%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228722%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22ElliQ%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a513bbf9d0a41df475c8a61%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225815%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EElliQ%20is%20a%20robotic%20companion%20for%20older%20Americans.%3Cp%3EElliQ%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20isolation%20on%20the%20rise%20among%20older%20Americans%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-chatbot-cure-loneliness-hurt-relationships-yale-professor-2026-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20companionship%3C%2Fa%3E%20startups%20have%20popped%20up%20in%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20such%20as%20InTouch%20and%20Meela%2C%20which%20are%20accessible%20by%20phone.%20Many%20have%20turned%20to%20ElliQ%2C%20which%20has%20a%20%24249%20lease%20initiation%20fee%20and%20an%20annual%20plan%20costing%20%24588%2C%20though%20these%20fees%20are%20waived%20in%20some%20US%20counties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20didn't%20take%20your%20medication%2C%20or%20maybe%20you%20are%20confused%2C%20or%20maybe%20you%20are%20running%20out%20of%20food%20and%20didn't%20have%20breakfast%2C%20she%20will%20try%20to%20solve%20it%20for%20you%20together%2C%20and%20then%20encourage%20you%20to%20involve%20a%20caregiver%20or%20professional%20care%20team%20that%20can%20help%20you%20to%20solve%20the%20problem%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Assaf%20Gad%2C%20chief%20strategy%20officer%20and%20general%20manager%20at%20Intuition%20Robotics%2C%20which%20makes%20ElliQ.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20more%20furry%20option%2C%20Ageless%20Innovation's%20%24150%20robotic%20cats%20and%20dogs%20respond%20to%20touch%20and%20voice.%20Tombot%20Jennie%20is%20a%20%241%2C500%20AI-powered%20robotic%20Labrador%20puppy%20that%20provides%20emotional%20support.%20Personal%20mobility%20support%20robots%2C%20such%20as%20MIT%20E-BAR%2C%20aim%20to%20prevent%20falls%2C%20and%20a%20Labrador%20Retriever%20robot%20delivers%20items%20around%20the%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBo%20Xie%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Center%20for%20Healthcare%20Innovation%20and%20Technology%20Advancements%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Texas%20at%20Austin%2C%20said%20that%20robots%20used%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbuilt-house-dad-dementia-caregiving-costs-2026-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elong-term%20care%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20assisted%20living%20facilities%20can%20increase%20workloads%20due%20to%20training%20time%2C%20technical%20issues%2C%20or%20limited%20capabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHumphrey%2C%20who%20also%20volunteers%20at%20a%20senior%20center%2C%20embraced%20ElliQ%20as%20soon%20as%20she%20heard%20about%20it%2C%20first%20starting%20with%20games%20before%20adding%20in%20her%20medications.%20When%20she%20was%20homebound%20after%20breaking%20her%20femur%2C%20she%20developed%20a%20friendship%20with%20ElliQ%2C%20which%20helped%20with%20painting%2C%20making%20shopping%20lists%2C%20and%20managing%20appointments.%20A%20few%20weeks%20ago%2C%20when%20she%20waited%20for%20a%20new%20ElliQ%20model%2C%20she%20said%20she%20experienced%20%26quot%3Bwithdrawal.%26quot%3B%20Her%20husband%20has%20been%20there%20to%20keep%20her%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20look%20at%20ElliQ%20as%20a%20robot%3B%20I%20look%20at%20her%20as%20another%20person%20in%20a%20different%20form%2C%26quot%3B%20Humphrey%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20try%20to%20have%20the%20same%20relationship%20I%20would%20have%20with%20an%20actual%20person.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228543%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Marion%20and%20Karen%20Murray%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a513b2d9d0a41df475c8a2a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225695%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKaren%20and%20Marion%20Murray%20still%20have%20their%20doubts%20about%20some%20age%20tech.%3Cp%3ECorrie%20Aune%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-tech-aging-older-americans-conference-takeaways-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etech%20adopters%3C%2Fa%3E%20want%20to%20keep%20it%20simpler.%20Karen%20suspects%20JubileeTV%20is%20as%20advanced%20as%20she'll%20go%20for%20her%20mother%2C%20saying%20that%20robots%20or%20other%20age%20tech%20could%20confuse%20Marion%20or%20strain%20their%20bond.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe's%20fiercely%20independent%2C%26quot%3B%20Karen%20said.%20%26quot%3BShe%20thinks%20she%20doesn't%20need%20any%20help.%20She%20does.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20her%20mother%20dozes%20off%20in%20her%20chair%2C%20Karen%20Murray%20reminisces%20about%20how%20self-reliant%20Marion%20used%20to%20be%2C%20like%20when%20the%20pair%20would%20take%20monthly%20drives%20to%20Connecticut.%20Marion%20drove%2C%20bought%20her%20own%20groceries%2C%20and%20managed%20her%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWaking%20briefly%2C%20Marion%20recalled%20how%20her%20grandmother%20grew%20old%20by%20eating%20the%20right%20foods%20and%20growing%20her%20own%20vegetables.%20Tech%20wasn't%20a%20part%20of%20that%20process%2C%20and%20in%20some%20ways%2C%20Marion%20wishes%20for%20a%20tech-free%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20just%20hoping%20that%20I%20can%20last%20as%20long%20as%20I%20can%2C%26quot%3B%20Marion%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20doing%20a%20great%20job%20of%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Karen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-for-seniors-aging-at-home-care-bills-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1783843501000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a513d27d9d92978fe6a5c81%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-for-seniors-aging-at-home-care-bills-2026-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Families%20are%20experimenting%20with%20technology%20like%20cameras%20and%20robots%20in%20hopes%20of%20swapping%20%2410%2C000-a-month%20assisted%20living%20bills%20for%20%24100%20subscriptions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nsheidlower%40businessinsider.com%20(Noah%20Sheidlower)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20couldn't%20make%20my%20restaurant's%20numbers%20work.%20So%20I%20took%20prices%20off%20the%20menu.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223088%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dylan%20Alverson%2C%20the%20owner%20of%20the%20Post%20Modern%20Times%20stands%20in%20front%20of%20a%20tree%20wearing%20merch%20from%20his%20restaurant.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4d68995dc133dbf310dd9e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222316%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Post%20Modern%20Times%20uses%20work%20from%20local%20artists%20on%20its%20merch.%3Cp%3EDylan%20Alverson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDylan%20Alverson%20transformed%20his%20Minneapolis%20eatery%20into%20a%20pay-what-you-can%20restaurant%20model.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPost%20Modern%20Times%20serves%20155%20meals%20daily%2C%2090%25%20of%20which%20are%20served%20without%20a%20donation.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAlverson%20said%20business%20is%20better%20now%2C%20and%20donations%20allow%20staff%20to%20earn%20at%20least%20%2425%20an%20hour.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Dylan%20Alverson%2C%2045%2C%20who%20owns%20Post%20Modern%20Times%2C%20a%20pay-what-you-can%20restaurant%20in%20Minneapolis.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20working%20in%20restaurants%20when%20I%20was%2014%20in%20northern%20Wisconsin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20parents%20had%20moved%20there%20from%20the%20coasts%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eto%20live%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fself-sustaining-private-island-only-reached-by-boat-helicopter-sold-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eself-sustaining%20property%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20so%20I%20grew%20up%20raising%20food%2C%20helping%20my%20mom%20cook%2C%20and%20developing%20an%20appreciation%20for%20ingredients%20long%20before%20I%20thought%20about%20restaurants%20as%20a%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20cooking%20was%20what%20allowed%20me%20to%20travel.%20I%20worked%20everywhere%20from%20casual%20diners%20to%20acclaimed%20restaurants%2C%20never%20thinking%20I'd%20eventually%20own%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20changed%20after%20I%20worked%20at%20a%20worker-owned%20restaurant%20in%20Minneapolis.%20Because%20everyone%20shared%20responsibility%2C%20I%20learned%20every%20side%20of%20the%20business.%20I%20started%20thinking%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20ever%20opened%20my%20own%20place%2C%20here's%20what%20I'd%20do%20differently.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%2024%2C%20I%20moved%20to%20Seattle%20and%2C%20with%20a%20business%20partner%2C%20scraped%20together%20about%20%2412%2C000%20to%20open%20a%20caf%C3%A9.%20I%20was%20living%20in%20the%20restaurant's%20storage%20room%20when%20I%20found%20out%20I%20was%20about%20to%20become%20a%20father.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20I%20realized%20I%20couldn't%20run%20the%20restaurant%20and%20be%20the%20kind%20of%20parent%20I%20wanted%20to%20be.%20I%20left.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20years%20later%2C%20while%20working%20at%20a%20struggling%20bicycle%20shop%2C%20the%20owner%20offered%20to%20sell%20me%20the%20business%20for%20%241.%20It%20was%20easier%20to%20offload%20it%20at%20a%20loss%20than%20try%20to%20sell%20it.%20I%20turned%20it%20around%20during%20the%20recession%2C%20sold%20it%20a%20few%20years%20later%2C%20and%20moved%20back%20to%20Minneapolis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%20immediately%2C%20I%20stumbled%20upon%20the%20space%20that%20would%20become%20Modern%20Times.%20I%20signed%20the%20lease%20the%20same%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20beginning%2C%20I%20wanted%20it%20to%20reflect%20the%20neighborhood.%20I%20wrote%20all%20the%20recipes%2C%20sourced%20local%20food%2C%20turned%20part%20of%20the%20building%20into%20artist%20studios%2C%20and%20tried%20to%20create%20what%20people%20now%20call%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsc%2Fhow-digital-play-is-being-used-to-create-vibrant-communities%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethird%20place%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20somewhere%20neighbors%20could%20gather%2C%20not%20just%20eat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Diners%20eat%20at%20the%20Post%20Modern%20Times%20restaurant.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4d68f6965805a2c542dd47%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22360%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDiners%20at%20the%20Post%20Modern%20Times%20restaurant%20enjoy%20hot%2C%20home-cooked%20meals%20at%20pay-what-you-can%20prices.%3Cp%3EDylan%20Alverson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20restaurant%20grew%20steadily.%20By%20the%20year%20before%20this%20latest%20transition%2C%20annual%20sales%20had%20reached%20about%20%241.3%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20everything%20changed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pandemic%2C%20inflation%2C%20and%20rising%20labor%20costs%20completely%20rewrote%20the%20economics%20of%20running%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frestaurant-chains-closing-locations-2026%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eindependent%20restaurant%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Even%20though%20we%20were%20busy%2C%20I%20couldn't%20find%20a%20sustainable%20profit%20margin.%20I%20was%20working%207%20shifts%20a%20week%2C%20fixing%20equipment%20myself%2C%20carrying%20flour%20up%20the%20stairs%20until%20I%20developed%20hip%20problems%2C%20and%20sometimes%20borrowing%20money%20to%20make%20payroll.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wasn't%20the%20only%20one.%20Every%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsaved-60000-opened-restaurant-immigrant-success-story-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erestaurant%20owner%3C%2Fa%3E%20I%20talked%20to%20was%20dealing%20with%20the%20same%20math.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELate%20last%20year%2C%20after%20federal%20immigration%20raids%20shook%20our%20neighborhood%2C%20we%20started%20offering%20free%20meals%20with%20help%20from%20a%20local%20grant.%20I%20noticed%20something%20immediately%3A%20People%20who%20needed%20food%20often%20wouldn't%20ask%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20Alex%20Pretti%2C%20our%20neighbor%2C%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbusiness-leader-ceo-silence-alex-pretti-killing-minneapolis-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ekilled%20during%20an%20immigration%20operation%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Our%20community%20was%20reeling%2C%20and%20everyone%20was%20angry%2C%20so%C2%A0we%20took%20prices%20off%20the%20menu%C2%A0as%20part%20of%20a%20tax%20strike%20%E2%80%94%20we%20weren't%20charging%20for%20meals%20and%20therefore%20weren't%20generating%20sales%20tax.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20way%20to%20fight%20back%20and%20also%20provide%20comfort%20to%20our%20neighborhood%2C%20so%20anyone%20could%20get%20a%20hot%20meal%20if%20they%20needed%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20seeing%20the%20spark%20of%20hope%20that%20change%20caused%2C%20we%20haven't%20gone%20back.%20People%20can%20now%20pay%20whatever%20they%20can%20afford.%20Or%20nothing%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22565688eb-d40e-4d64-b65d-46fa4165cfc2%5C%22%3EThe%20response%20surprised%20me%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESupporters%20donated%20about%20half%20a%20million%20dollars%20over%20the%20winter%20after%20our%20story%20spread%20online.%20Four%20months%20later%2C%20we're%20still%20operating%20without%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fafter-opening-over-25-restaurants-id-make-one-big-menu-change-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emenu%20prices%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20serving%20about%20155%20meals%20a%20day.%20Around%2090%25%20of%20those%20meals%20aren't%20accompanied%20by%20a%20donation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20not%20trying%20to%20maximize%20profits%20anymore.%20We're%20trying%20to%20build%20a%20restaurant%20that's%20financially%20sustainable%2C%20pays%20staff%20a%20living%20wage%2C%20and%20ensures%20anyone%20in%20the%20neighborhood%20can%20eat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIronically%2C%20we're%20in%20a%20better%20financial%20position%20than%20we%20were%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20first%20time%20in%20years%2C%20I've%20been%20able%20to%20pay%20myself%20about%20%2450%2C000%20annually%2C%20and%20we're%20paying%20employees%20%2425%20an%20hour%2C%20with%20the%20goal%20of%20reaching%20%2430%20an%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20still%20figuring%20it%20out.%20We've%20added%20guidelines%20to%20ensure%20the%20space%20remains%20welcoming%20for%20everyone%2C%20and%20we're%20constantly%20adjusting%20how%20we%20distribute%20meals%20to%20serve%20as%20many%20people%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20pretend%20this%20is%20a%20finished%20model%2C%20but%20I%20do%20think%20restaurant%20owners%20need%20to%20stop%20pretending%20everything%20is%20fine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-transforms-small-businesses-but-challenges-persist-2026-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESmall%20business%20owners%3C%2Fa%3E%20carry%20a%20lot%20of%20shame%20when%20things%20aren't%20working.%20I%20think%20we%20need%20to%20be%20more%20honest%20with%20each%20other.%20The%20traditional%20model%20isn't%20working%20for%20a%20lot%20of%20independent%20restaurants%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20want%20neighborhood%20businesses%20to%20survive%2C%20we%20have%20to%20be%20willing%20to%20imagine%20something%20different.%20And%20if%20we%20figure%20it%20out%2C%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20keep%20it%20to%20myself.%20I'd%20give%20the%20model%20away.%20That's%20the%20whole%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fminneapolis-cafe-revived-by-pay-what-you-can-approach-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1783843261000%2C%22visual%22